description.narrative: Enabling environment is strengthened to design, budget and implement evidence-based policies and strategies., which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The most vulnerable children and their families access improved quality and equitable health, nutrition and early intervention services

description.narrative: To inform policy and design targeted programs, availability of accurate and up-to-date data showing coverage of services, quality, gaps and challenges at provider as well as consumer side is critical, particularly focusing on the most vulnerable and marginalized populations in Jordan. A multi-agency (UNICEF, WFP and MOH) and national survey was conducted to assess the nutritional status of pre-school and school-aged children as well as women in reproductive age and inform the development of national strategy and action plan. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/08/2020
